{"index": 396, "title": "Senior Test Engineer", "job_location": "Bristol, England, United Kingdom", "jd_text": "Job SummaryQuality Assurance and Testing is an important part of the delivery of digital systems within the Health Research Authority. We have a team of skilled test professionals who make sure quality is delivered in the most effective way. We are looking to add automation engineering skills to our existing team as we value automating as much of the test effort as possible allowing our team of specialists to undertake better evaluations of the overall product set.As a Senior Test Engineer, you will create and drive the automated test engineering approach within the Research Systems Programme working closely with the Head of Test and other colleagues in the Agile development team. You will determine and implement automation approaches using Playwright(typescript) to assure, measure and build quality into every phase of the software life cycle. This involves developing or enhancing automation frameworks that help deliver scalable tests which are faster, frequent, and continuous. Job also involves performing manual testing where automation is not suitable.Main duties of the jobIdentify new and implement existing test automation frameworksWork on both functional and non-functional areas of complex system(s) built with multiple technologies (Microsoft, PEGA etc)Identify and raise awareness of defects, issues, risks arising from the automation test resultsBe proficient in a range of coding languages (C#, .Net, Java, JavaScript, Node, React, typescript etc)Work closely with members of Agile teamCollaborate with senior test analysts, business to make sure the required business scenarios are covered in the test scriptsCarry out system, integration and user acceptance testing using manual and automated techniquesLead on change impact assessment of all changes ensuring that test coverage mitigates any impact to external stakeholdersWork with the HRA's User Acceptanc