{"index": 423, "title": "Platform Support Engineer", "job_location": "Bristol, England, United Kingdom", "jd_text": "Job DescriptionLocation: Bristol or Edinburgh (Hybrid)In this position, you\u2019ll be based in either the Bristol or Edinburgh office for a minimum of three days a week, with the flexibility to work from home for some of your working week. Find out more about our flexible work culture at computershare.com/flex.We give you a world of potentialComputershare have an exciting opportunity to join our Technology Operations team, part of the wider Technology Services division, as a Platform Support Engineer.The Computershare Technology Operations group (CTO) is responsible for planning, designing, building and running technology services. The CTO teams span architecture, infrastructure, service operations, compliance and technical support. We ensure that colleagues around the world have access to the technology and agreed service levels that they need to take care of their clients and their clients\u2019 shareholders, employees and customers.In Technology Services (CTS) we partner with our global businesses, providing technology services and IT support and designing and developing new products to support our clients, customers and employees. Technology underpins everything we do as an organisation and is the engine driving our business forward.A role you will love The Platform Support Engineer plays a critical role, ensuring the seamless operation, deployment, and continuous improvement of both on-premises and cloud platforms. By collaborating with development, operations, and security teams, the engineer drives automation, standardization, and innovation across our technology stack.This role is central to maintaining high service availability, supporting internal projects, and delivering robust, scalable solutions that align with business objectives and customer needs.Platform Support Engineers are empowered to identify and implement process improvements, 